-- Kuwaiti Retailer Alshaya Seeks to Increase Stores, Chairman Says
-- B y   M a s s o u d   A .   D e r h a l l y
-- 2010-10-26T15:58:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-26/kuwaiti-retailer-alshaya-seeks-to-add-1-250-stores-over-next-five-years.html
M.H. Alshaya Co., a Kuwaiti retailer
with Middle East franchising rights for companies including
 Starbucks Corp.  and  Hennes & Mauritz AB , plans to open 1,250 new
stores over the next five years.  “We plan to do an average of 250 stores every year,”
Executive Chairman Mohammed Alshaya said in a phone interview
today from the World Economic Forum for the Middle East meeting
in Marrakech, Morocco. “The business is going to grow and
expand into 17 countries.”  Closely held M.H. Alshaya owns franchises for more than 55
retailers, according to its  website . It manages more than 1,800
stores in 15 countries including the Persian Gulf states,
Jordan, Lebanon, Russia, Egypt, Turkey, and central and eastern
Europe.  As well as Starbucks, the world’s largest coffee-shop
chain, Alshaya has franchise rights for stores including U.K.-
based retailers Alliance Boots Plc, Arcadia Group Plc and
Debenhams Plc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Massoud A. Derhally  in Beirut, Lebanon at   mderhally@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Peter Hirschberg at  phirschberg@bloomberg.net . 